content.description: Starts on a little roof and traverses left and diagonal to end near Dreamland's anchors.
content.location: Starts on the far right of Dreamer's Wall and traverses left around a rounded arête.

content.description: Hard bottom climbing leads to easy .10 moves up through the roof.
content.location: The route on the ledge that pulls a small roof. Just to the right of Open Spaces, shares 2 bolts with that route.

content.description: Traversing route on great hand holds with some sparse feet.
content.protection: 5 bolts, clip the sport anchors of The Arête Twins.
content.location: Just to the right of Eternal Love, shares bolt 2 of Water Quality.

content.description: 2 options include climbing the boltline, or climbing the right side of the dihedral.
content.location: First route to the right of the ledge that holds the previous 4 routes of the wall. Look for the obvious dihedral.

content.description: Left leaning hand crack, one route to the right of Huck of a Deal.
content.location: One route to the right of Huck of a Deal, starts after a small scramble up a ledge.

content.description: Bouldery start at the bottom, into easy 10 climbing. Hold can be a little sharp, and cryptic due to the little traffic on this route.
content.protection: 2 bolts, sport anchors out of sight.
content.location: First route on the wall, about 15 feet right on More Fun Than Bubble Wrap on Insanity Wall.

content.description:
Climbs the right side of the right arête and traverses the  wave feature to the Dreamland anchors.

 This route remains after the Lenora Reimer's Turkey Call anchors were removed.
content.location: The first bolt of this route is right where the access trail meets the wall. Right of L'arête Des Jumeaux (The Arête Twins) on the left side of the wave feature.
One right right of I Double-Dog-Adair Ya. Middle of the ledge you scramble up to start a few routes.

content.description: Very odd route that starts about 20 feet to the right of Lenora Reimer's Turkey Call. Look for a wave-like wall and a left leaning rail feature.
content.location: Second route from the right end of Dreamer's Wall.

content.description: This route is a variation that starts at the beginning of Eternal Love and traverses left after the first bolt and ends at the anchors for I Double-Dog-Adair Ya.  There are two bolts in-between those routes that are meant for this route.
content.location: Between Eternal Love and I Double-Dog-Adair Ya.

content.description: Fairly short wall, but has some decent routes and a few good warm ups for Insanity Wall just next door.
